UNDIAGNOSED ILLNESS - AFGHANISTAN: (PAKTIKA) REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 28 Dec 2017 23:45 AFT
Source: Pajhwok Afghan News [edited]
https://www.pajhwok.com/en/2017/12/28/2-paktika-children-die-mysterious-disease


Two children have died of a mysterious disease in Ziruk district of southeastern Paktika province, residents said on [Thu 28 Dec 2017].

The residents of Warjana village said the 2 children first developed flu, then increasing coughing and bleeding through mouth and nose.

[A resident] said the mysterious disease had concerned people. He said symptoms included flu, throat infection, high temperature, and diarrhea type signs. He said the disease had so far killed 2 children in the village.

A resident of Argun district said the Warjana village was located near them and the virus surfaced there about 5 days ago. Paktika public health director Dr Wali Gul said they had been informed about the disease and a team of doctors had been sent to the area for investigation. He said the outcome of the investigation would be shared with the media.

[Byline: Rahim Khan Khoshal]

